intel_vsec             20480  1 intel_pmc_core\nrapl                   20480  0\npmt_telemetry          16384  1 intel_pmc_core\ni2c_mux                16384  1 i2c_i801\nspi_intel_pci          12288  0\nsoundcore              16384  1 snd\nintel_cstate           24576  0\nwmi_bmof               12288  0\ngigabyte_wmi           12288  0\nspi_intel              32768  1 spi_intel_pci\ni2c_smbus              16384  1 i2c_i801\nmsr                    12288  0\npmt_class              16384  1 pmt_telemetry\nintel_hid              28672  0\nmei_me                 53248  0\nacpi_pad              184320  0\nsparse_keymap          12288  1 intel_hid\nacpi_tad               20480  0\nmei                   172032  1 mei_me\nmac_hid                12288  0\nparport_pc             53248  1\nppdev                  24576  0\nlp                     28672  0\nparport                73728  3 parport_pc,lp,ppdev\nefi_pstore             12288  0\nnfnetlink              20480  7 nft_compat,nf_conntrack_netlink,nf_tables,ip_set\ndmi_sysfs              24576  0\nip_tables              32768  0\nx_tables               65536  9 xt_conntrack,nft_compat,xt_tcpudp,xt_addrtype,xt                            _nat,xt_set,ip_tables,xt_MASQUERADE,xt_mark\nautofs4                57344  2\nhid_generic            12288  0\nusbhid                 77824  0\nhid                   262144  2 usbhid,hid_generic\namdgpu              19730432  1\namddrm_ttm_helper      12288  1 amdgpu\namdttm                114688  2 amdgpu,amddrm_ttm_helper\namddrm_buddy           24576  1 amdgpu\namdxcp                 12288  1 amdgpu\ndrm_exec               12288  1 amdgpu\ndrm_suballoc_helper    20480  1 amdgpu\namd_sched              61440  1 amdgpu\namdkcl                 32768  3 amd_sched,amdttm,amdgpu\ndrm_display_helper    278528  1 amdgpu\nnvme                   61440  1\ncec                    94208  2 drm_display_helper,amdgpu\nrc_core                73728  1 cec\ncrc32_pclmul           12288  0\nr8169                 118784  0\nnvme_core             221184  2 nvme\ni2c_algo_bit           16384  1 amdgpu\nahci                   49152  3\nintel_lpss_pci         28672  0\ndrm_ttm_helper         16384  1 amdgpu\nintel_lpss             12288  1 intel_lpss_pci\nxhci_pci               24576  0\nlibahci                53248  1 ahci\nrealtek                45056  1\nttm                   110592  1 drm_ttm_helper\nnvme_auth              28672  1 nvme_core\nidma64                 20480  0\nxhci_pci_renesas       20480  1 xhci_pci\nvideo                  77824  1 amdgpu\nwmi                    28672  3 video,gigabyte_wmi,wmi_bmof\npinctrl_alderlake      32768  0\njohn@ARM:~$\n\n\nThis is not fixed. Why is it closed? do I need to start a new issue??\r\n\r\n\r\nJM\r\n\r\n\r\nOn Fri, Jul 11, 2025 at 6:07\u202fAM Mtech ***@***.***> wrote:\r\n\r\n> Closed #1432\r\n> <https://github.com/automatic-ripping-machine/automatic-ripping-machine/issues/1432>\r\n> as completed via #1259\r\n> <https://github.com/automatic-ripping-machine/automatic-ripping-machine/pull/1259>\r\n> .\r\n>\r\n> \u2014\r\n> Reply to this email directly, view it on GitHub\r\n> <https://github.com/automatic-ripping-machine/automatic-ripping-machine/issues/1432#event-18584086437>,\r\n> or unsubscribe\r\n> <https://github.com/notifications/unsubscribe-auth/AGUAKIWQWUGIPXFN6JE2SMT3H6LGFAVCNFSM6AAAAACAEPMJIGVHI2DSMVQWIX3LMV45UABCJFZXG5LFIV3GK3TUJZXXI2LGNFRWC5DJN5XDWMJYGU4DIMBYGY2DGNY>\r\n> .\r\n> You are receiving this because you were mentioned.Message ID:\r\n> <automatic-ripping-machine/automatic-ripping-machine/issue/1432/issue_event/18584086437\r\n> @github.com>\r\n>\r\n\n@Bigjohn4 Ubuntu should have the `sg` kernel module because it's been part of the Linux kernel since the late 1990's. What happened when you tried the command `sudo modprobe sg`? `modprobe` usually only outputs errors, so if it outputted nothing, it probably worked. **Again, this command only temporarily loads the module until the next reboot.** If it didn't work, I honestly don't know. I said before I can't help you if the `sg` module doesn't work and I still stand by that. I simply don't have enough low-level knowledge. A quick web search took me to [this forum](https://askubuntu.com/questions/463644/why-is-a-scsi-disk-not-showing-up), which may or may not help. I use Arch, not Ubuntu, and I stopped using this project altogether recently so I'm not really that invested anymore either. There's a lot of design decisions that are just strange to me, like using `HandBrakeCLI` instead of `ffmpeg`, or worse, automatically down-mixing all audio to stereo by default (had to re-rip EVERYTHING because of this). The final straw for me is how the author is handling this issue, just closing it multiple times without checking with you to see if it's really fixed. \n\n@microtechno9000, I am now talking directly to you. I understand that life is busy and you are doing the majority of the work. I REALLY appreciate the effort you are putting into this project, as do many others. However, you are releasing this project publicly. Being busy is not an excuse to close issues without properly checking if the solution works or not, _especially_ when I was wrong and my suggestion didn't even work for OP. I'm a random person on the internet, you shouldn't trust me and just take what I say as the solution, that's why I linked the forum post and explained myself more. If you are spread too thin and don't have the time for this right now, that's understandable, but you need to communicate that. What's not understandable is closing issues that are not resolved as you have been doing with this one.\nit didnt trickle downstream enough for me to test, sadly\nAll\n\nThe issue was closed because I tagged it against a PR that was merged yesterday, so GitHub automatically closes the associated issue.\n\nBased on the work that ukos-git did with the PR, I was hoping that these issues would be resolved as the makemkv calls were modified\n\nIf all those affect by this issue could confirm the issue still remains post 2.17.x, I can take a look into why\nNot part of the original issue but I am still running into a similar issue even after upgrading to 2.17.x. ARM will find the disk, but then will freeze after starting MakeMKV. When I shell into the docker container and try to run any makemkvcon commands it also freezes.\n\nIt seems this might be a MakeMKV issue based on this forum post: https://forum.makemkv.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=3&t=37670\n\nRolling back to ARM 2.9.0 which uses an older version of MakeMKV has not given me the same issue and I am able to rip DVDs and Blu-Rays with no issues (abet using an older version of ARM).\n\nI would try to install an older version of MakeMKV (2.9.0 uses v1.17.8) in the 2.17.x Docker container, which might resolve the issue, but Docker is outside of my wheelhouse so I don't know where I would start with that.\n\n```[07-12-2025 10:54:50] INFO ARM: ******************* Logging config parameters *******************\n[07-12-2025 10:54:50] INFO ARM: skip_transcode: False\n[07-12-2025 10:54:50] INFO ARM: mainfeature: False\n[07-12-2025 10:54:50] INFO ARM: minlength: 600\n[07-12-2025 10:54:50] INFO ARM: maxlength: 6000\n[07-12-2025 10:54:50] INFO ARM: videotype: auto\n[07-12-2025 10:54:50] INFO ARM: manual_wait: True\n[07-12-2025 10:54:50] INFO ARM: manual_wait_time: 180\n[07-12-2025 10:54:50] INFO ARM: ripmethod: mkv\n[07-12-2025 10:54:50] INFO ARM: mkv_args: \n[07-12-2025 10:54:50] INFO ARM: delrawfiles: True\n[07-12-2025 10:54:50] INFO ARM: hb_preset_dvd: H.265 NVENC 1080p\n[07-12-2025 10:54:50] INFO ARM: hb_preset_bd: H.265 NVENC 2160p 4K\n[07-12-2025 10:54:50] INFO ARM: hb_args_dvd: --subtitle scan -F\n[07-12-2025 10:54:50] INFO ARM: hb_args_bd: --subtitle scan -F --subtitle-burned --audio-lang-list eng --all-audio\n[07-12-2025 10:54:50] INFO ARM: raw_path: /home/arm/media/raw/\n[07-12-2025 10:54:50] INFO ARM: transcode_path: /home/arm/media/transcode/\n[07-12-2025 10:54:50] INFO ARM: completed_path: /home/arm/media/completed/\n[07-12-2025 10:54:50] INFO ARM: extras_sub: extras\n[07-12-2025 10:54:50] INFO ARM: emby_refresh: False\n[07-12-2025 10:54:50] INFO ARM: emby_server: \n[07-12-2025 10:54:50] INFO ARM: emby_port: 8096\n[07-12-2025 10:54:50] INFO ARM: notify_rip: True\n[07-12-2025 10:54:50] INFO ARM: notify_transcode: True\n[07-12-2025 10:54:50] INFO ARM: max_concurrent_transcodes: 0\n[07-12-2025 10:54:50] INFO ARM: max_concurrent_makemkvinfo: 0\n[07-12-2025 10:54:50] INFO ARM: ******************* End of config parameters *******************\n[07-12-2025 10:54:50] INFO ARM: Checking for fstab entry.\n[07-12-2025 10:54:50] INFO ARM: fstab entry is: /dev/sr0  /mnt/dev/sr0  udf,iso9660  users,noauto,exec,utf8,ro  0  0\n[07-12-2025 10:54:50] INFO ARM: Final Output directory \"/home/arm/media/transcode/unidentified/SBSP_THE_PILOT_A_MINI_MOVIE (2015)\"\n[07-12-2025 10:54:50] INFO ARM: Final Output directory \"/home/arm/media/completed/unidentified/SBSP_THE_PILOT_A_MINI_MOVIE (2015)\"\n[07-12-2025 10:54:50] INFO ARM: Processing files to: /home/arm/media/transcode/unidentified/SBSP_THE_PILOT_A_MINI_MOVIE (2015)\n[07-12-2025 10:54:50] INFO ARM: ************* Ripping disc with MakeMKV *************\n[07-12-2025 10:54:51] INFO ARM: Updating MakeMKV key...\n[07-12-2025 10:54:51] INFO ARM: Starting MakeMKV rip. Method is mkv```\nI don't think the issue is with ARM but with MakeMKV. All was working until\r\nmy BetaKey expired and I upgraded MakeMKV to latest version. I am going to\r\nlook for a way to run previous version without having to pay $60 to try it.\r\nThanks for all your time and effort. I'll update as soon as I am able to\r\ntest again. Likely a week or so. Other projects get in the way \ud83d\ude00\r\n\r\n\r\nJM\r\n\r\n\r\nOn Sat, Jul 12, 2025 at 9:01\u202fAM Mtech ***@***.***> wrote:\r\n\r\n> *microtechno9000* left a comment\r\n> (automatic-ripping-machine/automatic-ripping-machine#1432)\r\n> <https://github.com/automatic-ripping-machine/automatic-ripping-machine/issues/1432#issuecomment-3065545180>\r\n>\r\n> All\r\n>\r\n> The issue was closed because I tagged it against a PR that was merged\r\n> yesterday, so GitHub automatically closes the associated issue.\r\n>\r\n> Based on the work that ukos-git did with the PR, I was hoping that these\r\n> issues would be resolved as the makemkv calls were modified\r\n>\r\n> \u2014\r\n> Reply to this email directly, view it on GitHub\r\n> <https://github.com/automatic-ripping-machine/automatic-ripping-machine/issues/1432#issuecomment-3065545180>,\r\n> or unsubscribe\r\n> <https://github.com/notifications/unsubscribe-auth/AGUAKIWDXCOOJ5JIL5F5WVT3IEIKFAVCNFSM6AAAAACAEPMJIGVHI2DSMVQWIX3LMV43OSLTON2WKQ3PNVWWK3TUHMZTANRVGU2DKMJYGA>\r\n> .\r\n> You are receiving this because you were mentioned.Message ID:\r\n> <automatic-ripping-machine/automatic-ripping-machine/issues/1432/3065545180\r\n> @github.com>\r\n>\r\n\nI have not heard from anyone on MakeMKV forum with an answer. \nAny more ideas here? I truly don't want to just start over or give up. Must be a fix of some sort.\nNever got any ideas, so I decided to update Automatic Ripping Machine (ARM). \nI clicked on the \"Update Available\" link and let it update. \nThen put in a DVD and let it run. It did not run long before system crashed. On reboot, Ubuntu got a kernel panic and would not start. I tried recovery options, but no luck. So I reinstalled Ubuntu, Docker and ARM. Fortunately my config files were all on another file system so Arm started back up okay. I then put in DVD, and everything is working again. I have processed several DVDs and all seems to be working again. \n\nA bit brute force, but it is working again.\nThanks for the help. and I'll close cases. \nthanks for all the help\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/automatic-ripping-machine/automatic-ripping-machine/commit/4ef2cff43cd78c88af1f34f61b254f1d06a237ca", "https://github.com/automatic-ripping-machine/automatic-ripping-machine/commit/d93