 \"WorkDir\" : \"/var/lib/docker/overlay2/385c504e2c1ba10002e2b7f798f152a6afdf8a9f603ce8e171e31b85d889b057/work\"\n    },\n    \"Name\" : \"overlay2\"\n  },\n  \"RootFS\" : {\n    \"Type\" : \"layers\",\n    \"Layers\" : [ \"sha256:e0a9f5911802534ba097660206feabeb0247a81e409029167b30e2e1f2803b57\", \"sha256:826feaeeb19264d37a426dc52e9590c053294eec9d1f0c97314794b14d014486\", \"sha256:6e15c7129ef9fa5fa631097efa913dd8f96751986237078c240bd973d06fb36e\", \"sha256:ef1f4aade700d262bb52706a71d4e8bc83fdcea26f2783da7816f9c300b3cd1a\", \"sha256:5f70bf18a086007016e948b04aed3b82103a36bea41755b6cddfaf10ace3c6ef\", \"sha256:3c0b9c83b658707e78183bf0e1043a3ff94ba645e15cbb75f176b13536d946da\", \"sha256:3a006394d1a7386a4f6e869d9266691a7619a9b03ada899f80a38e485219844a\", \"sha256:37a966d21e6f382cd9d40b6e931c0e0194f9ffde5203d0b355a4564bbc6f8afb\", \"sha256:4c9879ca9fba80faca1bdcf91be0a96b6a9cdcbe925b5537a32575522eb2115f\", \"sha256:d38cac133bfc994d33e5b9139800793b61c8455bea1a16b780d58a61aab93867\", \"sha256:d3a80bbfe108eca959532dde9c04a746c98982614eb9b3f5c91681c9549e8baf\", \"sha256:341dfbb932de362aa4e21dbb6608009dcfb41ba42fda21d570a7ebae11ebd0fa\", \"sha256:0b8017a8606255e49fa221b92ca01f1125c1340194559b0a285e27a896ba5430\", \"sha256:d4c6d636c8725e75bc26b41a0d1eba53465e4e51dbb600154cc3acf58eb45bc9\", \"sha256:647439a1eb5d4a62eb088ac125d67c6f5c686bc14409a3efd4d9694a5b520aa9\", \"sha256:4653e815c994a8b1160e449041e4859679ee4b7cf3eec831347f35c929e50307\", \"sha256:10f9dcd7fcbb1fa50bc1ccedc4e9c435e78951effe56a82ce8db5132d42b1397\", \"sha256:1e676d724f1df611e7782141f88f9adf96f3324fed242a8eea695fe83d16f958\", \"sha256:20f12b616cfb31228671dca9f6ee4d6b96c17d2738eded5c1e1fb38c2d0b87ff\", \"sha256:c76e2aefd9fcc91e3848985b434604c34d85a69dda8e1ee06484165dfe97aea4\", \"sha256:e221d1f664eacca6c111f2dc8f6a8a1c586b3aa6e9682887837ef20dd0198dbf\", \"sha256:e5503927846ea6e9c7d9ea6f16ffd6c03b27abed8f2954cbaaf7ee2d757df1be\", \"sha256:fac28a21d72c2518bbbdcae9b43a75c8a8c0ed86cb88df89ed9a25353921a04a\", \"sha256:a0129ffb8f335393630673884bcbb4b9c08da27e42d206a63b2603fc338e3a9e\", \"sha256:ffe28f6afbf2572fcefce939f9d98b23377790580120bacf8113ad6d0127c52b\", \"sha256:f72c4fb1b2c6357016638970418f68430f691201cfe87d4a063a1d1709566d7e\", \"sha256:52bd1473d233ac60ff9ac5433395242a5bb57b9557b6b44dc6561feb5d9625a4\", \"sha256:d24d849381a05d97c29b1035e70b4b17b3bf80896e7459e896c25e7312a4b07d\", \"sha256:32d5a7ac416929e98c575538b078e6a3bc36e43823774d979adf588b1195b326\", \"sha256:5f70bf18a086007016e948b04aed3b82103a36bea41755b6cddfaf10ace3c6ef\", \"sha256:5f70bf18a086007016e948b04aed3b82103a36bea41755b6cddfaf10ace3c6ef\", \"sha256:8104933f79cfcadb9fd23cc465fa45a6d28f8df8c7d253422d3e9a046ebe574d\", \"sha256:fe6f4401d8c07b2bf2a8c9a9ce489369b8f5d79052191bea7f543ae80a42b282\", \"sha256:5f70bf18a086007016e948b04aed3b82103a36bea41755b6cddfaf10ace3c6ef\", \"sha256:766fe32179b46e7416e0bd6a14dcb1e3ed255da3d7fe5e0bde19fa1bbf6bcccf\", \"sha256:5f70bf18a086007016e948b04aed3b82103a36bea41755b6cddfaf10ace3c6ef\", \"sha256:a73c44518df2b3ce758d2c77102f2a73d732843cef2e91e7cb69d294b0ce844d\", \"sha256:c92e8e89e4b4dc38126cabeb0be915873b43d6379cac8bb949aaa823e5996418\", \"sha256:3f3f991b946bc6064e6c6cc7bcc38e97a3e7820444351b2aec699237e4eea85a\", \"sha256:5f70bf18a086007016e948b04aed3b82103a36bea41755b6cddfaf10ace3c6ef\" ]\n  },\n  \"Metadata\" : {\n    \"LastTagTime\" : \"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z\"\n  }\n}\n```\nHere is when I build the container...\n\n```\nroot@kozlak:/docker/arm# docker compose build\n[+] Building 4.3s (21/21) FINISHED                                                                               \n => [internal] load local bake definitions                                                                  0.0s\n => => reading from stdin 539B                                                                              0.0s\n => CACHED [internal] load git source https://github.com/automatic-ripping-machine/automatic-ripping-machi  0.6s\n => [internal] load metadata for docker.io/automaticrippingmachine/arm-dependencies:1.6.2                   0.4s\n => CACHED [base  1/12] FROM docker.io/automaticrippingmachine/arm-dependencies:1.6.2@sha256:9cbe20a4fa915  0.0s \n => [base  2/12] RUN     mkdir -m 0777 -p /home/arm     /home/arm/config /mnt/dev/sr0     /mnt/dev/sr1 /mn  0.2s \n => [base  3/12] RUN rm -rf /etc/service/sshd /etc/my_init.d/00_regen_ssh_host_keys.sh                      0.2s\n => [base  4/12] RUN mkdir /etc/service/armui                                                               0.2s\n => [base  5/12] COPY ./scripts/docker/runsv/armui.sh /etc/service/armui/run                                0.1s\n => [base  6/12] RUN chmod +x /etc/service/armui/run                                                        0.2s\n => [base  7/12] RUN mkdir -p /etc/my_init.d                                                                0.2s\n => [base  8/12] COPY ./scripts/docker/runit/arm_user_files_setup.sh /etc/my_init.d/arm_user_files_setup.s  0.1s\n => [base  9/12] COPY ./scripts/docker/runit/start_udev.sh /etc/my_init.d/start_udev.sh                     0.1s\n => [base 10/12] RUN chmod +x /etc/my_init.d/*.sh                                                           0.2s\n => [base 11/12] COPY ./scripts/docker/custom_udev /etc/init.d/udev                                         0.1s\n => [base 12/12] RUN chmod +x /etc/my_init.d/*.sh                                                           0.2s\n => [automatic-ripping-machine 1/4] COPY . /opt/arm/                                                        0.1s\n => [automatic-ripping-machine 2/4] RUN ln -sv /opt/arm/setup/51-docker-arm.rules /lib/udev/rules.d/        0.2s\n => [automatic-ripping-machine 3/4] RUN git config --global --add safe.directory /opt/arm                   0.2s\n => [automatic-ripping-machine 4/4] WORKDIR /home/arm                                                       0.1s\n => exporting to image                                                                                      0.4s\n => => exporting layers                                                                                     0.3s\n => => writing image sha256:77ed7725330ad28eba526688676d9b00b7ff2afc4a891bad43836a2acac9fe2b                0.0s\n => => naming to docker.io/local/arm:latest                                                                 0.0s\n => resolving provenance for metadata file                                                                  0.0s\n[+] Building 1/1\n \u2714 local/arm:latest  Built                    \n```\n\nStill just passes the arm-dependencies tags to the main image for whatever reason.\nYou would need to pass in the tags yourself to update the completed image. Or just set them in your Dockerfile.\n\n\nFor a more complete answer, the arm dependency repo doesn't set this correctly, but even if it did, it wouldn't match the final build version of arm anyway as they use different version numbers. For instance, the latest version of arm-deps is 1.6.2, but the latest version of the complete docker is 2.20.5.\n\nThe repo for the dependencies is depreciated in 3.0, so it doesn't receive that many updates, despite needing a lot of work.\nOk, so if I grab the image directly, it does work (just tried that). However, if I build a local image using the image as context, it doesnt pass all of the Labels from the other images. Very odd. My use case is that I want to add extra stuff into my images like support for QSV.\n\nWill tinker with this, to see if there is a way to get the Labels passed through, as it may help others.\nYeah, this is because if you put the values directly in the Dockerfile they are static and need updated manually, or a complex script.  But we use GitHub actions to deploy our final images so it automatically adds the tags for us.\n\nIf it's just for you, you can manually set the tags in the container via Dockerfile like this \n\nhttps://docs.docker.com/reference/dockerfile/#label\nAdd this to your final Dockerfile you compose with (at the bottom so you can test/change them easily while testing)\n```\nLABEL org.opencontainers.image.source=https://github.com/automatic-ripping-machine/utomatic-ripping-machine/.git\nLABEL org.opencontainers.image.url=https://github.com/automatic-ripping-machine/utomatic-ripping-machine/\nLABEL org.opencontainers.image.description=\"Automatic Ripping Machine - with Intel quicksync\"\nLABEL org.opencontainers.image.documentation=https://raw.githubusercontent.com/automatic-ripping-machine/utomatic-ripping-machine/README.md\nLABEL org.opencontainers.image.license=MIT\nLABEL org.opencontainers.image.version=2.55.55\nLABEL org.opencontainers.image.created=20251022\n```\n\nPS.\nIf you fork this repo, you can make your changes and run the action to have it built for you. This would fix the tagging issue without the need to manually change it every time. With the added bonus of automatic deployment.\nThanks for this information! A few things that others may benefit from if they stumble upon this thread:\n- While you cannot pass LABELs directly, you can inherit them in a way...\n```\n    build:\n      context: 'https://github.com/automatic-ripping-machine/automatic-ripping-machine.git'\n      labels:\n        org.opencontainers.image.description: 'ARM w/ Intel Quick Sync Video Support (Intel Media Stack)'\n      dockerfile_inline: |\n        FROM automaticrippingmachine/automatic-ripping-machine:latest AS base\n        LABEL org.opencontainers.image.description=\"ARM w/ Intel Quick Sync Video Support (Intel Media Stack)\"\n        RUN apt update -y &&\\\n          apt upgrade -y &&\\\n          apt install -y intel-media-va-driver-non-free libigdgmm12 &&\\\n          cd /tmp &&\\\n          mkdir -p quicksync && cd quicksync &&\\\n          git clone https://github.com/Intel-Media-SDK/MediaSDK msdk &&\\\n          mkdir -p build-msdk && cd build-msdk &&\\\n          cmake ../msdk &&\\\n          make && make install &&\\\n          cd ../.. &&\\\n          rm -r quicksync\n      no_cache: true\n```\nGiven the other fix you had done previously, the version shows up...\n```\nroot@kozlak:/docker/arm# docker image inspect local/arm:latest | grep org.opencontainers.image.\n                \"org.opencontainers.image.created\": \"2025-10-22T00:43:45.483Z\",\n                \"org.opencontainers.image.description\": \"ARM w/ Intel Quick Sync Video Support (Intel Media Stack)\",\n                \"org.opencontainers.image.documentation\": \"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/automatic-ripping-machine/arm-dependencies/main/README.md\",\n                \"org.opencontainers.image.license\": \"MIT\",\n                \"org.opencontainers.image.licenses\": \"MIT\",\n                \"org.opencontainers.image.ref.name\": \"ubuntu\",\n                \"org.opencontainers.image.revision\": \"20cd4ee96962cd7161f5231611e00b87fed0382c\",\n                \"org.opencontainers.image.source\": \"https://github.com/automatic-ripping-machine/automatic-ripping-machine\",\n                \"org.opencontainers.image.title\": \"automatic-ripping-machine\",\n                \"org.opencontainers.image.url\": \"https://github.com/automatic-ripping-machine/automatic-ripping-machine\",\n                \"org.opencontainers.image.version\": \"2.20.5\"\n```\n- When custom building.. it is also possible to use arguments via a generated .env file that goes along with the docker-compose.yml and those can be dynamically referenced.\n\n@1337-server Note that somewhere in your build, you may have a typo since you are adding both 'license' and 'licenses':\n```\n                \"org.opencontainers.image.license\": \"MIT\",\n                \"org.opencontainers.image.licenses\": \"MIT\",\n```\n\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/automatic-ripping-machine/automatic-ripping-machine/commit/2b4874741a1e03025293fa17d60eca0ffe14e50d", "https://github.com/automatic-ripping-machine/automatic-ripping-machine/commit/35a3b13ab0b9c77e9d85591c42bf9d76a304dbef", "https://github.com/automatic-ripping-machine/automatic-ripping-machine/commit/059c213dd6de33881b99677024748ddeb6e58ac3", "https://github.com/automatic-ripping-machine/automatic-ripping-machine/commit/11312b64acedfcfe8b263fe60b365e33a6ed0403"], "created_at": "2025-10-02T11:20:38Z"}
{"repo": "automatic-ripping-machine/automatic-ripping-machine", "pull_number": 1458, "instance_id": "automatic-ripping-machine__automatic-ripping-machine-1458", "issue_numbers": [1454], "base_commit": "1588f9c9db2d72459c8ce8307f445b79da51bf5e", "patch": "diff --git a/VERSION b/VERSION\nindex 94c60781e..94dc0ec91 100755\n--- a/VERSION\n+++ b/VERSION\n@@ -1,1 +1,1 @@\n-2.17.1\n\\ No newline at end of file\n+2.17.2\ndiff --git a/arm/models/system_drives.py b/arm/models/system_drives.py\nindex 5a88eaab0..026269a66 100644\n--- a/arm/models/system_drives.py\n+++ b/arm/models/system_drives.py\n@@ -272,6 +272,8 @@ def release_current_job(self):\n         logging.info(\"Releasing current job from drive\")\n         # Preserve as previous job\n         self.job_id_previous = self.job_id_current\n+        # Resetting current job to None in order to release it\n+        self.job_id_current = None\n \n     def new_job(self, job_id):\n         \"\"\"new job assigned to the drive, update with new job id, and previous job_id\"\"\"\ndiff --git a/arm/ui/forms.py b/arm/ui/forms.py\nindex 9ec099f9d..ff6224411 100755\n--- a/arm/ui/forms.py\n+++ b/arm/ui/forms.py\n@@ -2,7 +2,7 @@\n from flask_wtf import FlaskForm\n from wtforms import StringField, SubmitField, SelectField, \\\n     IntegerField, BooleanField, PasswordField, Form, FieldList, FormField, HiddenField\n-from wtforms.validators import DataRequired\n+from wtforms.validators import DataRequired, Optional\n \n \n class TitleSearchForm(FlaskForm):\n@@ -82,7 +82,7 @@ class SystemInfoDrives(FlaskForm):\n     \"\"\"\n     id = IntegerField('Drive ID', validators=[DataRequired()])\n     name = StringField('Name', validators=[DataRequired()])\n-    description = StringField('Description', validators=[DataRequired()])\n+    description = StringField('Description', validators=[Optional()])\n     drive_mode = SelectField('Drive Mode',\n                              validators=[DataRequired()],\n                              choices=[\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "\ud83d\udc1b Jobs Not Releasing\n### Is there an existing issue for this?\n\n- [x] I have searched the existing issues\n\n### I have checked the wiki\n\n- [x] I have searched the wiki for this problem\n\n### Does this issue exist in the latest version?\n\n- [x] I'm using the latest release\n\n### Describe the bug?\n\nSee the following in DEBUG logs:\n\n```\n[07-11-2025 14:13:57] DEBUG ARM: utils.database_adder successfully written Notifications to the database\n[07-11-2025 14:13:57] INFO ARM: arm_ripper.rip_visual_media ************* ARM processing complete *************\n[07-11-2025 14:13:57] INFO ARM: job.eject Skipping auto eject\n[07-11-2025 14:13:57] INFO ARM: system_drives.release_current_job Releasing current job from drive\n```\n\nRip is completed, but shows that the job is still in progress.\n\n<img width=\"604\" height=\"282\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d76fced1-92a0-4412-bcdf-52ca2f54bacf\" />\n\nManual eject via the button provides an error: Job [23] in progress. Cannot eject 1. This persists with rebooting the host and restarting the container. Popping out / in a new disc has no effect.\n\nTrying to abandon the job doesnt work either:\n\n<img width=\"345\" height=\"94\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/072f26dd-426f-4efa-a888-ab85f6359aee\" />\n\nOnly way to recover was to delete the job.\n\nThe AUTO_EJECT setting was set to False. Setting it to True has no effect. The disk does eject after ripping, but the job does not clear after encoding.\n\n### To Reproduce\n\nSee above.\n\n### What OS are you seeing the problem on?\n\nall\n\n### ARM Release Version or Git hash (You can find this in the arm settings page)\n\nPython version: 3.10.12\nA.R.M version: 2.17.0\nCurrent git version: 30f5a9e\n\n### Expected behavior?\n\nJob should clear, instead of hanging and subsequent being held up until the job is manually deleted.\n\n### Relevant log output\n\n```shell\n\n```\n\n### Anything else?\n\n_No response_\n\n### Code of Conduct\n\n- [x] I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct\n", "hints_text": "Here is the error thrown when a new disc is tossed in..\n\n```\n[07-11-2025 22:02:19] INFO ARM: ARMInfo.get_values ARM version: 2.17.0\n[07-11-2025 22:02:19] INFO ARM: ARMInfo.get_values Python version: 3.10.12 (main, May 27 2025, 17:12:29) [GCC 11.4.0]\n[07-11-2025 22:02:19] INFO ARM: ARMInfo.get_values User is: arm\n[07-11-2025 22:02:19] INFO ARM: ARMInfo.get_values Alembic head is: a79af75f4b31\n[07-11-2025 22:02:19] INFO ARM: ARMInfo.get_values Database version is: a79af75f4b31\n[07-11-2025 22:02:19] CRITICAL ARM: utils.duplicate_run_check Drive /dev/sr0 has an active Job (23): success.\n[07-11-2025 22:02:19] INFO ARM: utils.duplicate_run_check Job was started {job_time}min ago.\n```\n\n", "all_hints_text": "Here is the error thrown when a new disc is tossed in..\n\n```\n[07-11-2025 22:02:19] INFO ARM: ARMInfo.get_values ARM version: 2.17.0\n[07-11-2025 22:02:19] INFO ARM: ARMInfo.get_values Python version: 3.10.12 (main, May 27 2025, 17:12:29) [GCC 11.4.0]\n[07-11-2025 22:02:19] INFO ARM: ARMInfo.get_values User is: arm\n[07-11-2025 22:02:19] INFO ARM: ARMInfo.get_values Alembic head is: a79af75f4b31\n[07-11-2025 22:02:19] INFO ARM: ARMInfo.get_values Database version is: a79af75f4b31\n[07-11-2025 22:02:19] CRITICAL ARM: utils.duplicate_run_check Drive /dev/sr0 has an active Job (23): success.\n[07-11-2025 22:02:19] INFO ARM: utils.duplicate_run_check Job was started {job_time}min ago.\n```\nStill see the same error (on latest code) when I abandon a job... I have one DVD failing transcoding with 0fps being done on each update. So I clicked abandon. Threw in a new disc, and same problem...\n\n```\n[07-15-2025 16:05:16] CRITICAL ARM: utils.duplicate_run_check Drive /dev/sr0 has an active Job (24): fail.\n[07-15-2025 16:05:16] INFO ARM: utils.duplicate_run_check Job was started {job_time}min ago.\n```\n\nPython version: 3.10.12\nA.R.M version: 2.17.2\nCurrent git version: 181ff05\nIssue reopened to review issue when abandoning jobs\nI ran into this issue too, but for me, when testing, waiting more than 3 minutes made ARM find the disk\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/automatic-ripping-machine/automatic-ripping-machine/commit/ed81b222e282e4d7a464ec561d1879b38b297b19", "https://github.com/automatic-ripping-machine/automatic-ripping-machine/commit/9625d51e68465f782e82af4c7463c9a7a38d2368", "https://github.com/automatic-ripping-machine/automatic-ripping-machine/commit/84d4687a70193b1fb722047bcfd9cdbf304dba91"], "created_at": "2025-07-13T17:22:57Z"}
{"repo": "automatic-ripping-machine/automatic-ripping-machine", "pull_number": 1488, "instance_id": "automatic-ripping-machine__automatic-ripping-machine-1488", "issue_numbers": [1484], "base_commit": "c6f5df4465fa5f8ae28c8bc44806bd819a7bfe22", "patch": "diff --git a/arm/ripper/makemkv.py b/arm/ripper/makemkv.py\nindex 779a889e3..efaae6e3d 100644\n--- a/arm/ripper/makemkv.py\n+++ b/arm/ripper/makemkv.py\n@@ -755,8 +755,7 @@ def rip_mainfeature(job, track, rawpath):\n         job: arm.models.job.Job\n         track: arm.models.track.Track\n     \"\"\"\n-    logging.info(\"Processing track#{num} as mainfeature. Length is {seconds}s\",\n-                 num=track.track_number, seconds=track.length)\n+    logging.info(f\"Processing track#{track.track_number} as mainfeature. Length is {track.length}s\")\n     filepathname = os.path.join(rawpath, track.filename)\n     logging.info(f\"Ripping track#{track.track_number} to {shlex.quote(filepathname)}\")\n     cmd = [\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Unable to rip any DVD. ERROR ARM: MakeMKV did not complete successfully.\nNo matter what DVD I try, I always end up with this error. See log file.\n\n\n```\n[07-27-2025 17:42:54] INFO ARM: ************* Ripping disc with MakeMKV *************\n[07-27-2025 17:42:54] INFO ARM: Updating MakeMKV key...\n[07-27-2025 17:42:54] INFO ARM: Starting MakeMKV rip. Method is mkv\n[07-27-2025 17:42:54] INFO ARM: MakeMKV disc number: 0\n[07-27-2025 17:42:54] INFO ARM: Destination is /home/arm/media/raw/AU_REVOIR_LES_ENFANTS\n[07-27-2025 17:42:54] INFO ARM: Processing files to: /home/arm/media/raw/AU_REVOIR_LES_ENFANTS\n[07-27-2025 17:42:54] INFO ARM: Job running in auto mode\n[07-27-2025 17:44:04] INFO ARM: Found 3 titles\n[07-27-2025 17:44:04] INFO ARM: MakeMKV exits gracefully.\n[07-27-2025 17:44:04] INFO ARM: MakeMKV info exits.\n[07-27-2025 17:44:04] INFO ARM: Trying to find mainfeature\n[07-27-2025 17:44:04] ERROR ARM: MakeMKV did not complete successfully.  Exiting ARM! Error: Logger._log() got an unexpected keyword argument 'num'\n[07-27-2025 17:44:04] ERROR ARM: \nTraceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"/opt/arm/arm/ripper/arm_ripper.py\", line 56, in rip_visual_media\n    makemkv_out_path = makemkv.makemkv(job)\n  File \"/opt/arm/arm/ripper/makemkv.py\", line 694, in makemkv\n    makemkv_mkv(job, rawpath)\n  File \"/opt/arm/arm/ripper/makemkv.py\", line 626, in makemkv_mkv\n    rip_mainfeature(job, track, rawpath)\n  File \"/opt/arm/arm/ripper/makemkv.py\", line 710, in rip_mainfeature\n    logging.info(\"Processing track#{num} as mainfeature. Length is {seconds}s\",\n  File \"/usr/lib/python3.10/logging/__init__.py\", line 2138, in info\n    root.info(msg, *args, **kwargs)\n  File \"/usr/lib/python3.10/logging/__init__.py\", line 1477, in info\n    self._log(INFO, msg, args, **kwargs)\nTypeError: Logger._log() got an unexpected keyword argument 'num'\n\nThe above exception was the direct cause of the following exception:\n\nTraceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"/opt/arm/arm/ripper/main.py\", line 225, in <module>\n    main(log_file, job, args.protection)\n  File \"/opt/arm/arm/ripper/main.py\", line 111, in main\n    arm_ripper.rip_visual_media(have_dupes, job, logfile, protection)\n  File \"/opt/arm/arm/ripper/arm_ripper.py\", line 60, in rip_visual_media\n    raise ValueError from mkv_error\nValueError\n[07-27-2025 17:44:04] ERROR ARM: A fatal error has occurred and ARM is exiting.  See traceback below for details.\n[07-27-2025 17:44:07] INFO ARM: Releasing current job from drive\n```\n\n\nFresh docker install.\nOutput of `lsscsi -g`\n\n\n```\n$ lsscsi -g\n[1:0:0:0]    cd/dvd  hp       CDDVDW SH-216DB  HH20  /dev/sr0   /dev/sg0 \n[2:0:0:0]    disk    ATA      TK0120GDJXT      HPG0  /dev/sda   /dev/sg1 \n[5:0:0:0]    disk    Generic- USB3.0 CRW-CF/MD 1.00  /dev/sdb   /dev/sg2 \n[5:0:0:1]    disk    Generic- USB3.0 CRW-SD    1.00  /dev/sdc   /dev/sg3 \n[5:0:0:2]    disk    Generic- USB3.0 CRW-MS    1.00  /dev/sdd   /dev/sg4 \n```\n\n", "hints_text": "He Issue lies in an incorrectly formatted logging message --> Must be an **f-String**. In the file\n`/opt/arm/arm/ripper/makemkv.py`\ninside the function\n`def rip_mainfeature(job, track, rawpath):`\nchange the following line (close to line 710-711)\n`logging.info(\"Processing track#{num} as mainfeature. Length is {seconds}s\",`\nto\n`logging.info(f\"Processing track#{num} as mainfeature. Length is {seconds}s\",`\nNote the **f**\"...\"\n\n", "all_hints_text": "He Issue lies in an incorrectly formatted logging message --> Must be an **f-String**. In the file\n`/opt/arm/arm/ripper/makemkv.py`\ninside the function\n`def rip_mainfeature(job, track, rawpath):`\nchange the following line (close to line 710-711)\n`logging.info(\"Processing track#{num} as mainfeature. Length is {seconds}s\",`\nto\n`logging.info(f\"Processing track#{num} as mainfeature. Length is {seconds}s\",`\nNote the **f**\"...\"\nDuplicate of #1465\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/automatic-ripping-machine/automatic-ripping-machine/commit/382eac9ee945377ec3f4288525aea30968e18899", "https://github.com/automatic-ripping-machine/automatic-ripping-machine/commit/680d556c5b3e7e9d9a6dd4fe8dd52975505886e8", "https://github.com/automatic-ripping-machine/automatic-ripping-machine/commit/961e81b58ce22d1c1263e53a311b19d3c96ec716", "https://github.com/automatic-ripping-machine/automatic-ripping-machine/commit/3e100bb91e4173c909db05602c32ff3c493ac9a0", "https://github.com/automatic-ripping-machine/automatic-ripping-machine/commit/123f43a41c032735f128d5819418fe6426a6a546", "https://github.com/automatic-ripping-machine/automatic-ripping-machine/commit/260533a85e43400e5a01e70bb7a9b25b65186e48"], "created_at": "2025-07-30T10:14:47Z"}
{"repo": "automatic-ripping-machine/automatic-ripping-machine", "pull_number": 1501, "instance_id": "automatic-ripping-machine__automatic-ripping-machine-1501", "issue_numbers": [1496], "base_commit": "a5862512ccf0b1894832ee4210c907212fe675f3", "patch": "diff --git a/VERSION b/VERSION\nindex cf8690732..a36e9b090 100755\n--- a/VERSION\n+++ b/VERSION\n@@ -1,1 +1,1 @@\n-2.18.0\n+2.18.1\ndiff --git a/arm/ripper/makemkv.py b/arm/ripper/makemkv.py\nindex 64c3c6854..a7200702a 100644\n--- a/arm/ripper/makemkv.py\n+++ b/arm/ripper/makemkv.py\n@@ -157,8 +157,14 @@ class MessageID(enum.IntEnum):\n     Please purchase an activation key if you've found this application useful.\n     You may still use all free functionality without any restrictions.\n     \"\"\"\n+    EVALUATION_PERIOD_EXPIRED_APP_TOO_OLD = 5021\n+    \"\"\"This application version is too old.  Please download the latest version\n+    at http://www.makemkv.com/ or enter a registration key to continue using\n+    the current version.\n+    \"\"\"\n     EVALUATION_PERIOD_EXPIRED_SHAREWARE = 5055\n     \"\"\"Evaluation period has expired, shareware functionality unavailable.\"\"\"\n+\n     RIP_BACKUP_FAILED_PRE = 5096\n     RIP_BACKUP_FAILED = 5080\n     \"\"\"Backup Mode Failed.\"\"\"\n@@ -1000,6 +1006,7 @@ class MakeMKVOutputChecker:\n     }\n \n     SPECIAL_ERROR_CODES = {\n+        MessageID.EVALUATION_PERIOD_EXPIRED_APP_TOO_OLD,\n         MessageID.EVALUATION_PERIOD_EXPIRED_SHAREWARE,\n         MessageID.RIP_BACKUP_FAILED,\n     }\n@@ -1051,6 +1058,8 @@ def write_error(self):\n         return MakeMKVErrorMessage(*dataclasses.astuple(self.data), self.data.message)\n \n     def special_error_code(self):\n+        \"\"\"These Errors are typically critical\"\"\"\n+        logging.critical(self.data.message)\n         return MakeMKVErrorMessage(*dataclasses.astuple(self.data), self.data.message)\n \n     def log_only_code(self):\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "\ud83d\udc0b <title>A.R.M. ripp of DVD or BlueRay fails. MakeMKV error code 253.\n### Is there an existing issue for this?\n\n- [x] I have searched the existing issues\n\n### Does this issue exist in the latest version?\n\n- [x] I'm using the latest release\n\n### Describe the bug?\n\nafter no fix for my case #1432, I reinstalled Ubuntu 24.04LTS. Then installed latest docker and latest A.R.M download. First 5 DVDs processed correctly. Next day, I tried more. They all get MakeMKV error 253.\nI then cleaned both DVD and BluRay drives. Still fails.\nWhat is error #253?\n\n### To Reproduce\n\nTry and DVD or BluRay.\n\n### Built from source files ?\n\n- [ ] I Built the image from source\n\n### What architecture are you seeing the problem on?\n\namd64\n\n### Expected behavior?\n\nI expect it to work.\n\n### Relevant log output\n\n```shell\nLoading log: ALLOFME.log...\n\n[08-01-2025 21:09:44] INFO ARM: ARM version: 2.17.5\n[08-01-2025 21:09:44] INFO ARM: Python version: 3.10.12 (main, May 27 2025, 17:12:29) [GCC 11.4.0]\n[08-01-2025 21:09:44] INFO ARM: User is: arm\n[08-01-2025 21:09:44] INFO ARM: Alembic head is: a79af75f4b31\n[08-01-2025 21:09:44] INFO ARM: Database version is: a79af75f4b31\n[08-01-2025 21:09:44] INFO ARM: ************* Starting ARM processing at 2025-08-01 21:09:44.141003 *************\n[08-01-2025 21:09:45] INFO ARM: Creating new job for drive.\n[08-01-2025 21:09:45] INFO ARM: Looking for log files older than 1 days old.\n[08-01-2025 21:09:45] INFO ARM: Checking path /home/arm/logs/ for old log files...\n[08-01-2025 21:09:45] INFO ARM: Checking path /home/arm/logs/progress for old log files...\n[08-01-2025 21:09:45] INFO ARM: Job: ALLOFME\n[08-01-2025 21:09:45] INFO ARM: Job #142 with PID 285 is currently running.\n[08-01-2025 21:09:45] INFO ARM: Starting Disc identification\n[08-01-2025 21:09:45] INFO ARM: Mounting disc to: /mnt/dev/sr0\n[08-01-2025 21:09:45] INFO ARM: Mounting disc was successful\n[08-01-2025 21:09:45] INFO ARM: Disc identified as video\n[08-01-2025 21:09:45] INFO ARM: DVD CRC64 hash is: e9cb8f98ce33a69a\n[08-01-2025 21:09:46] INFO ARM: Disc title Post ident -  title:ALLOFME year:None video_type:unknown disctype: dvd\n[08-01-2025 21:09:46] INFO ARM: We have no previous rips/jobs matching this label\n[08-01-2025 21:09:46] INFO ARM: Waiting 60 seconds for manual override.\n[08-01-2025 21:10:21] INFO ARM: Manual override found.  Overriding auto identification values.\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: ******************* Logging ARM variables *******************\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: devpath: /dev/sr0\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: mountpoint: /mnt/dev/sr0\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: title: All of Me\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: year: 1984\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: video_type: movie\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: hasnicetitle: True\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: label: ALLOFME\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: disctype: dvd\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: manual_start: False\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: ******************* End of ARM variables *******************\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: ******************* Logging config parameters *******************\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: skip_transcode: False\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: mainfeature: False\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: minlength: 600\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: maxlength: 99999\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: videotype: auto\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: manual_wait: True\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: manual_wait_time: 60\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: ripmethod: mkv\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: mkv_args: \n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: delrawfiles: True\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: hb_preset_dvd: HQ 720p30 Surround\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: hb_preset_bd: HQ 1080p30 Surround\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: hb_args_dvd: --subtitle scan -F\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: hb_args_bd: --subtitle scan -F --subtitle-burned --audio-lang-list eng --all-audio\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: raw_path: /home/arm/media/raw/\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: transcode_path: /home/arm/media/transcode/\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: completed_path: /home/arm/media/completed/\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: extras_sub: extras\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: emby_refresh: False\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: emby_server: \n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: emby_port: 8096\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: notify_rip: True\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: notify_transcode: True\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: max_concurrent_transcodes: 0\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: max_concurrent_makemkvinfo: 0\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: ******************* End of config parameters *******************\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: Checking for fstab entry.\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: fstab entry is: /dev/sr0  /mnt/dev/sr0  udf,iso9660  users,noauto,exec,utf8,ro  0  0\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: Final Output directory \"/home/arm/media/transcode/movies/All of Me (1984)\"\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: Final Output directory \"/home/arm/media/completed/movies/All of Me (1984)\"\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: Processing files to: /home/arm/media/transcode/movies/All of Me (1984)\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: ************* Ripping disc with MakeMKV *************\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: Updating MakeMKV key...\n[08-01-2025 21:10:22] INFO ARM: Starting MakeMKV rip. Method is mkv\n[08-01-2025 21:10:23] ERROR ARM: Call to MakeMKV failed with code: 253\n[08-01-2025 21:10:23] INFO ARM: MakeMKV info exits.\n[08-01-2025 21:10:23] ERROR ARM: MakeMKV did not complete successfully.  Exiting ARM! Error: Call to MakeMKV failed with code: 253\n[08-01-2025 21:10:23] ERROR ARM: \nTraceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"/opt/arm/arm/ripper/arm_ripper.py\", line 56, in rip_visual_media\n    makemkv_out_path = makemkv.makemkv(job)\n  File \"/opt/arm/arm/ripper/makemkv.py\", line 681, in makemkv\n    for drive in get_drives(job):\n  File \"/opt/arm/arm/ripper/makemkv.py\", line 581, in get_drives\n    for drive in makemkv_info(job, select=OutputType.DRV):\n  File \"/opt/arm/arm/ripper/makemkv.py\", line 559, in makemkv_info\n    yield from run(info_options, select)\n  File \"/opt/arm/arm/ripper/makemkv.py\", line 1108, in run\n    raise MakeMkvRuntimeError(proc.returncode, cmd, output=os.linesep.join(buffer))\narm.ripper.makemkv.MakeMkvRuntimeError: Call to MakeMKV failed with code: 253\n\nThe above exception was the direct cause of the following exception:\n\nTraceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"/opt/arm/arm/ripper/main.py\", line 225, in <module>\n    main(log_file, job, args.protection)\n  File \"/opt/arm/arm/ripper/main.py\", line 111, in main\n    arm_ripper.rip_visual_media(have_dupes, job, logfile, protection)\n  File \"/opt/arm/arm/ripper/arm_ripper.py\", line 60, in rip_visual_media\n    raise ValueError from mkv_error\nValueError\n[08-01-2025 21:10:23] ERROR ARM: A fatal error has occurred and ARM is exiting.  See traceback below for details.\n[08-01-2025 21:10:23] ERROR ARM: eject: cannot open /dev/sr0: Device or resource busy\n\n[08-01-2025 21:10:23] INFO ARM: Releasing current job from drive\n\nAutomatic Ripping Machine. Find us on github.\n```\n\n### Anything else?\n\nam I just snake bit?\n\n### Code of Conduct\n\n- [x] I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct\n", "hints_text": "I have the exact same issue/error. Tried DVD and Bluray. Tried complete reset up from scratch. No dice.\nIn fact my logs look identical, minus the Movie name :)\n\nI believe this is due to the beta key for makemkv expiring at the end of July but am not sure\nI'm having the exact same issue, and yeah, I also strongly suspect it's the beta key that has expired which MakeMKV uses. I tested this by turning back the pc clock by one day yesterday as chatgpt suggested, but I'm not using it as a permanent measure as I don't feel morally right deceiving the authors intention. Not sure when the new key will come out, waiting. \nUsing MakeMkv docker container and ARM both stopped working for me. This is not a BETA key issue as I have a full license and its not working for me either. \nI hope someone from MakeMKV group is reading this. Seems it is broken for some reason.\nI was considering buying a license, but that doesn't seem to fix the issue. I am still willing to purchase a license, but only if MakeMKV group verifies that will make their product more stable.\nThanks for the updates. Hopefully we will get an answer soon.\nthis is also happening to me today. haven't used ARM in a few weeks, so idk when it started, but i can confirm it's happened on the latest version and this bug also occurred on version 2.17.2 before i updated, but only since today. and version 2.17.2 worked fine for me up until today too\n+1 to this. I just updated my ARM instance without checking the latest issues (silly me), and now it's broken, erroring out with 253. Even a fresh OS, Docker, and ARM installation still throws the same error. I am even willing to pay for a MakeMKV license to avoid the beta key shenanigans, but even MakeMKV's payment portal is down.\nJust trying to point the owner in the right direction, I helped resolve this issue with another ripping container.\n\n\nThe config file key was not properly used when checking available drives (thus registered key was not used).\n\nPlease check to make sure this is not the issue with the ARM image. \nAfter checking the MakeMKV forums it's likely the expiration of the MakeMKV beta key. However I purchased a permeant key this morning, have not received it yet, and several have said they haven't received theirs either. Once (if) I get my key, I'll add it and test again. A possible work around is to set your date on your OS back several weeks and see if \"tricking\" MakeMKV will temporarily fix it.\n`timedatectl set-ntp no\n`\n`timedatectl set-time 2025-7-10`\n\nJust tested this and worked for me, but as I said this will only temporarily fix the issue until MakeMKV owner can reset the beta key again. Good luck!\n> After checking the MakeMKV forums it's likely the expiration of the MakeMKV beta key. However I purchased a permeant key this morning, have not received it yet, and several have said they haven't received theirs either. Once (if) I get my key, I'll add it and test again. A possible work around is to set your date on your OS back several weeks and see if \"tricking\" MakeMKV will temporarily fix it.\n\nI have a permanent key for ARM and it's not working either... I think there is a beta key stuck somewhere and not being changed via Config\nI made a fix that can be used with the docker version of ARM without having to change your system time. All I did was add this to the Dockerfile just above `CMD [\"/sbin/my_init\"]`:\n```Dockerfile\nRUN apt-get update && \\\n    apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends libfaketime && \\\n    ln -s $(ldconfig -p | grep libfaketime | head -n1 | awk '{print $4}') \\\n          /usr/local/lib/libfaketime.so\n\n################################################################\nRUN mv \"/usr/local/bin/makemkv\" \"/usr/local/bin/makemkv_orig\"\nRUN mv \"/usr/local/bin/makemkvcon\" \"/usr/local/bin/makemkvcon_orig\"\n\nRUN printf '%s\\n' \\\n           '#!/bin/bash' \\\n           'env FAKETIME=\"2025-07-27 03:01:29\" FAKETIME_DONT_FAKE_MONOTONIC=1 FAKETIME_NO_SIMULATE_SIGSEGV=1 LD_PRELOAD=/usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/faketime/libfaketime.so.1 /usr/local/bin/makemkvcon_orig $@' > /usr/local/bin/makemkvcon && chmod +x /usr/local/bin/makemkvcon\n\nRUN printf '%s\\n' \\\n           '#!/bin/bash' \\\n           'env FAKETIME=\"2025-07-27 03:01:29\" FAKETIME_DONT_FAKE_MONOTONIC=1 FAKETIME_NO_SIMULATE_SIGSEGV=1 LD_PRELOAD=/usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/faketime/libfaketime.so.1 /usr/local/bin/makemkv_orig $@' > /usr/local/bin/makemkv && chmod +x /usr/local/bin/makemkv\n```\n\nIt installs faketime, renames `makemkv` and `makemkvcon`  to `makemkv_orig` and `makemkvcon_orig`, and creates wrapper scripts that use faketime to set the time to July 27 2025 when calling makemkv. I tried it out and it does work. \n\n\n\nI uploaded a docker image to docker.io with the patch added, so all you need to do is modify your `start_arm_container.sh` file to use `nickc0101/arm_mkv_faketime:latest`.\n```sh\n#!/bin/bash\ndocker run -d \\\n    -p \"8080:8080\" \\\n    -e ARM_UID=\"1001\" \\\n    -e ARM_GID=\"1002\" \\\n    -e TZ=\"New_York\" \\\n    -v \"/home/arm:/home/arm\" \\\n    -v \"/home/arm/music:/home/arm/music\" \\\n    -v \"/home/arm/logs:/home/arm/logs\" \\\n    -v \"/home/arm/media:/home/arm/media\" \\\n    -v \"/home/arm/config:/etc/arm/config\" \\\n    --device=\"/dev/sr0:/dev/sr0\" \\\n    --device=\"/dev/sr1:/dev/sr1\" \\\n    --privileged \\\n    --restart \"always\" \\\n    --name \"arm-rippers\" \\\n    --cpuset-cpus='0-24' \\\n    nickc0101/arm_mkv_faketime:latest # USE THIS IMAGE INSTEAD\n```\nSame error. Re-installed makemkv in the container with the provided script, ran it, got a reg key error, set the permanent reg key on the command line, makemkvcon ran fine manually after that but not with ARM. I have `MAKEMKV_PERMA_KEY` set in settings.\n\nWhen I run the makemkvcon command from the log in the container it runs file.\n\n```\n[08-03-2025 00:56:34] INFO ARM: ARMInfo.get_values ARM version: 2.17.5\n[08-03-2025 00:56:34] INFO ARM: ARMInfo.get_values Python version: 3.10.12 (main, May 27 2025, 17:12:29) [GCC 11.4.0]\n[08-03-2025 00:56:34] INFO ARM: ARMInfo.get_values User is: arm\n[08-03-2025 00:56:34] INFO ARM: ARMInfo.get_values Alembic head is: a79af75f4b31\n[08-03-2025 00:56:34] INFO ARM: ARMInfo.get_values Database version is: a79af75f4b31\n[08-03-2025 00:56:34] INFO ARM: main.<module> ************* Starting ARM processing at 2025-08-03 00:56:34.467899 *************\n...\n[08-03-2025 00:57:37] DEBUG ARM: utils.database_updater successfully written to the database\n[08-03-2025 00:57:37] DEBUG ARM: arm_ripper.rip_visual_media Using MakeMKV: [True]\n[08-03-2025 00:57:37] INFO ARM: arm_ripper.rip_visual_media ************* Ripping disc with MakeMKV *************\n[08-03-2025 00:57:37] INFO ARM: makemkv.prep_mkv Updating MakeMKV key...\n[08-03-2025 00:57:37] DEBUG ARM: makemkv.prep_mkv MAKEMKV_PERMA_KEY populated, using that...\n[08-03-2025 00:57:37] DEBUG ARM: makemkv.prep_mkv b''\n[08-03-2025 00:57:37] INFO ARM: makemkv.makemkv Starting MakeMKV rip. Method is mkv\n[08-03-2025 00:57:37] DEBUG ARM: makemkv.makemkv Storing new MakeMKV disc numbers to database.\n[08-03-2025 00:57:37] DEBUG ARM: makemkv.run command: '/usr/local/bin/makemkvcon --robot --messages=-stdout info --cache=1 disc:9999'\n[08-03-2025 00:57:37] DEBUG ARM: makemkv.run PID 286: command: '/usr/local/bin/makemkvcon --robot --messages=-stdout info --cache=1 disc:9999'\n[08-03-2025 00:57:37] DEBUG ARM: makemkv.run MSG:1005,0,1,\"MakeMKV v1.18.1 linux(x64-release) started\",\"%1 started\",\"MakeMKV v1.18.1 linux(x64-release)\"\n[08-03-2025 00:57:37] DEBUG ARM: makemkv.run MakeMKVMessage(code=1005, flags=0, count=1, message='MakeMKV v1.18.1 linux(x64-release) started', sprintf=['%1 started', 'MakeMKV v1.18.1 linux(x64-release)'])\n[08-03-2025 00:57:37] DEBUG ARM: makemkv.run MSG:5021,131332,1,\"This application version is too old.  Please download the latest version at http://www.makemkv.com/ or enter a registration key to continue using the current version.\",\"This application version is too old.  Please download the latest version at %1 or enter a registration key to continue using the current version.\",\"http://www.makemkv.com/\"\n[08-03-2025 00:57:37] DEBUG ARM: makemkv.run MakeMKVMessage(code=5021, flags=131332, count=1, message='This application version is too old.  Please download the latest version at http://www.makemkv.com/ or enter a registration key to continue using the current version.', sprintf=['This application version is too old.  Please download the latest version at %1 or enter a registration key to continue using the current version.', 'http://www.makemkv.com/'])\n[08-03-2025 00:57:37] DEBUG ARM: makemkv.run <_io.TextIOWrapper name=9 encoding='UTF-8'>\n[08-03-2025 00:57:37] DEBUG ARM: makemkv.__init__ MakeMKV command: '/usr/local/bin/makemkvcon --robot --messages=-stdout info --cache=1 disc:9999'\n[08-03-2025 00:57:37] DEBUG ARM: makemkv.__init__ MakeMKV output: \n[08-03-2025 00:57:37] ERROR ARM: makemkv.__init__ Call to MakeMKV failed with code: 253\n```\n\nForum post:\n```\n[MakeMKV is free while in beta](https://forum.makemkv.com/forum/viewtopic.php?p=3548&sid=417bf48acf94b45f48ab4950fa20018a#p3548)\n\nPost by [mike admin](https://forum.makemkv.com/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&u=3&sid=417bf48acf94b45f48ab4950fa20018a) \u00bb Thu Mar 04, 2010 4:46 am\nAs stated on a main page all features of MakeMKV are free while program is in beta.\n\nThe current beta key is\n\nCode: [Select all](https://forum.makemkv.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=5&t=1053#)\n\nT-iyhMMBV8nWtNo3BgMdcvypH8UL01nYmww2zFzQDtiZsdJUOaAuCURsPRQ1Hj3i75RE\n\nand is valid until end of July 2025. Please check back for updated key on this page.\n```\n\nRunning `bash /opt/arm/scripts/update_key.sh` with my permanent key and commenting out `prep_mkv()` from `makemkv.py` was a successful workaround.\nWhere can I put the beta key? \nI don't have the update_key.sh.\n\nroot@ARM:/home/john# ls /opt/arm/scripts\nls: cannot access '/opt/arm/scripts': No such file or directory\nroot@ARM:/home/john#\n\n\nFound config file in .MakeMKV/settings.conf and put in key above. Still fails with same code.\n\nwill try restarting docker and see if that helps.\n\nStop and restart docker made no difference.\n\nBy the way, I don't see any mention of the key in the log. In the past, MakeMKV always said something about the key when it started up, I think. Don't have any old logs to look at but I seem to remember that.\n@Bigjohn4 This beta key will not work unless you set your system date back to July. It doesn't seem that a new beta key has been released. My workaround uses a purchased permanent key.\nI still suspect there's a bug in how ARM applies the registration key from the configuration that uses the beta key even when a permanent key is specified, but I haven't been able to spot it. \n> [@Bigjohn4](https://github.com/Bigjohn4) This beta key will not work unless you set your system date back to July. It doesn't seem that a new beta key has been released. My workaround uses a purchased permanent key.\n\nSeems like the timing is bad to get one of those, as the store link doesn't open for me to buy one \n\n<img width=\"1104\" height=\"347\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/abfebc33-ea89-4851-91d8-c5b3cc7f8a5d\" />\nAny updates on this issue. Seems like this is still broken when I try to Rip a DVD\n@showcasefloyd try @nickc01 's time travel workaround if you are using the beta key. That is not a problem with ARM. You'll just need to wait until the MakeMVK maintainer updates it.\n\nIf you have purchased a key, try the workaround I posted.\n\n", "all_hints_text": "I have the exact same issue/error. Tried DVD and Bluray. Tried complete reset up from scratch. No dice.\nIn fact my logs look identical, minus the Movie name :)\n\nI believe this is due to the beta key for makemkv expiring at the end of July but am not sure\nI'm having the exact same issue, and yeah, I also strongly suspect it's the beta key that has expired which MakeMKV uses. I tested this by turning back the pc clock by one day yesterday as chatgpt suggested, but I'm not using it as a permanent measure as I don't feel morally right deceiving the authors intention. Not sure when the new key will come out, waiting. \nUsing MakeMkv docker container and ARM both stopped working for me. This is not a BETA key issue as I have a full license and its not working for me either. \nI hope someone from MakeMKV group is reading this. Seems it is broken for some reason.\nI was considering buying a license, but that doesn't seem to fix the issue. I am still willing to purchase a license, but only if MakeMKV group verifies that will make their product more stable.\nThanks for the updates. Hopefully we will get an answer soon.\nthis is also happening to me today. haven't used ARM in a few weeks, so idk when it started, but i can confirm it's happened on the latest version and this bug also occurred on version 2.17.2 before i updated, but only since today. and version 2.17.2 worked fine for me up until today too\n+1 to this. I just updated my ARM instance without checking the latest issues (silly me), and now it's broken, erroring out with 253. Even a fresh OS, Docker, and ARM installation still throws the same error. I am even willing to pay for a MakeMKV license to avoid the beta key shenanigans, but even MakeMKV's payment portal is down.\nJust trying to point the owner in the right direction, I helped resolve this issue with another ripping container.\n\n\nThe config file key was not properly used when checking available drives (thus registered key was not used).\n\nPlease check to make sure this is not the issue with the ARM image. \nAfter checking the MakeMKV forums it's likely the expiration of the MakeMKV beta key. However I purchased a permeant key this morning, have not received it yet, and several have said they haven't received theirs either. Once (if) I get my key, I'll add it and test again. A possible work around is to set your date on your OS back several weeks and see if \"tricking\" MakeMKV will temporarily fix it.\n`timedatectl set-ntp no\n`\n`timedatectl set-time 2025-7-10`\n\nJust tested this and worked for me, but as I said this will only temporarily fix the issue until MakeMKV owner can reset the beta key again. Good luck!\n> After checking the MakeMKV forums it's likely the expiration of the MakeMKV beta key. However I purchased a permeant key this morning, have not received it yet, and several have said they haven't received theirs either. Once (if) I get my key, I'll add it and test again. A possible work around is to set your date on your OS back several weeks and see if \"tricking\" MakeMKV will temporarily fix it.\n\nI have a permanent key for ARM and it's not working either... I think there is a beta key stuck somewhere and not being changed via Config\nI made a fix that can be used with the docker version of ARM without having to change your system time. All I did was add this to the Dockerfile just above `CMD [\"/sbin/my_init\"]`:\n```Dockerfile\nRUN apt-get update && \\\n    apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends libfaketime && \\\n    ln -s $(ldconfig -p | grep libfaketime | head -n1 | awk '{print $4}') \\\n          /usr/local/lib/libfaketime.so\n\n################################################################\nRUN mv \"/usr/local/bin/makemkv\" \"/usr/local/bin/makemkv_orig\"\nRUN mv \"/usr/local/bin/makemkvcon\" \"/usr/local/bin/makemkvcon_orig\"\n\nRUN printf '%s\\n' \\\n           '#!/bin/bash' \\\n           'env FAKETIME=\"2025-07-27 03:01:29\" FAKETIME_DONT_FAKE_MONOTONIC=1 FAKETIME_NO_SIMULATE_SIGSEGV=1 LD_PRELOAD=/usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/faketime/libfaketime.so.1 /usr/local/bin/makemkvcon_orig $@' > /usr/local/bin/makemkvcon && chmod +x /usr/local/bin/makemkvcon\n\nRUN printf '%s\\n' \\\n           '#!/bin/bash' \\\n           'env FAKETIME=\"2025-07-27 03:01:29\" FAKETIME_DONT_FAKE_MONOTONIC=1 FAKETIME_NO_SIMULATE_SIGSEGV=1 LD_PRELOAD=/usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/faketime/libfaketime.so.1 /usr/local/bin/makemkv_orig $@' > /usr/local/bin/makemkv && chmod +x /usr/local/bin/makemkv\n```\n\nIt installs faketime, renames `makemkv` and `makemkvcon`  to `makemkv_orig` and `makemkvcon_orig`, and creates wrapper scripts that use faketime to set the time to July 27 2025 when calling makemkv. I tried it out and it does work. \n\n\n\nI uploaded a docker image to docker.io with the patch added, so all you need to do is modify your `start_arm_container.sh` file to use `nickc0101/arm_mkv_faketime:latest`.\n```sh\n#!/bin/bash\ndocker run -d \\\n    -p \"8080:8080\" \\\n    -e ARM_UID=\"1001\" \\\n    -e ARM_GID=\"1002\" \\\n    -e TZ=\"New_York\" \\\n    -v \"/home/arm:/home/arm\" \\\n    -v \"/home/arm/music:/home/arm/music\" \\\n    -v \"/home/arm/logs:/home/arm/logs\" \\\n    -v \"/home/arm/media:/home/arm/media\" \\\n    -v \"/home/arm/config:/etc/arm/config\" \\\n    --device=\"/dev/sr0:/dev/sr0\" \\\n    --device=\"/dev/sr1:/dev/sr1\" \\\n    --privileged \\\n    --restart \"always\" \\\n    --name \"arm-rippers\" \\\n    --cpuset-cpus='0-24' \\\n    nickc0101/arm_mkv_faketime:latest # USE THIS IMAGE INSTEAD\n```\nSame error. Re-installed makemkv in the container with the provided script, ran it, got a reg key error, set the permanent reg key on the command line, makemkvcon ran fine manually after that but not with ARM. I have `MAKEMKV_PERMA_KEY` set in settings.\n\nWhen I run the makemkvcon command from the log in the container it runs file.\n\n```\n[08-03-2025 00:56:34] INFO ARM: ARMInfo.get_values ARM version: 2.17.5\n[08-03-2025 00:56:34] INFO ARM: ARMInfo.get_values Python version: 3.10.12 (main, May 27 2025, 17:12:29) [GCC 11.4.0]\n[08-03-2025 00:56:34] INFO ARM: ARMInfo.get_values User is: arm\n[08-03-2025 00:56:34] INFO ARM: ARMInfo.get_values Alembic head is: a79af75f4b31\n[08-03-2025 00:56:34] INFO ARM: ARMInfo.get_values Database version is: a79af75f4b31\n[08-03-2025 00:56:34] INFO ARM: main.<module> ************* Starting ARM processing at 2025-08-03 00:56:34.467899 *************\n...\n[08-03-2025 00:57:37] DEBUG ARM: utils.database_updater successfully written to the database\n[08-03-2025 00:57:37] DEBUG ARM: arm_ripper.rip_visual_media Using MakeMKV: [True]\n[08-03-2025 00:57:37] INFO ARM: arm_ripper.rip_visual_media ************* Ripping disc with MakeMKV *************\n[08-03-2025 00:57:37] INFO ARM: makemkv.prep_mkv Updating MakeMKV key...\n[08-03-2025 00:57:37] DEBUG ARM: makemkv.prep_mkv MAKEMKV_PERMA_KEY populated, using that...\n[08-03-2025 00:57:37] DEBUG ARM: makemkv.prep_mkv b''\n[08-03-2025 00:57:37] INFO ARM: makemkv.makemkv Starting MakeMKV rip. Method is mkv\n[08-03-2025 00:57:37] DEBUG ARM: makemkv.makemkv Storing new MakeMKV disc numbers to database.\n[08-03-2025 00:57:37] DEBUG ARM: makemkv.run command: '/usr/local/bin/makemkvcon --robot --messages=-stdout info --cache=1 disc:9999'\n[08-03-2025 00:57:37] DEBUG ARM: makemkv.run PID 286: command: '/usr/local/bin/makemkvcon --robot --messages=-stdout info --cache=1 disc:9999'\n[08-03-2025 00:57:37] DEBUG ARM: makemkv.run MSG:1005,0,1,\"MakeMKV v1.18.1 linux(x64-release) started\",\"%1 started\",\"MakeMKV v1.18.1 linux(x64-release)\"\n[08-03-2025 00:57:37] DEBUG ARM: makemkv.run MakeMKVMessage(code=1005, flags=0, count=1, message='MakeMKV v1.18.1 linux(x64-release) started', sprintf=['%1 started', 'MakeMKV v1.18.1 linux(x64-release)'])\n[08-03-2025 00:57:37] DEBUG ARM: makemkv.run MSG:5021,131332,1,\"This application version is too old.  Please download the latest version at http://www.makemkv.com/ or enter a registration key to continue using the current version.\",\"This application version is too old.  Please download the latest version at %1 or enter a registration key to continue using the current version.\",\"http://www.makemkv.com/\"\n[08-03-2025 00:57:37] DEBUG ARM: makemkv.run MakeMKVMessage(code=5021, flags=131332, count=1, message='This application version is too old.  Please download the latest version at http://www.makemkv.com/ or enter a registration key to continue using the current version.', sprintf=['This application version is too old.  Please download the latest version at %1 or enter a registration key to continue using the current version.', 'http://www.makemkv.com/'])\n[08-03-2025 00:57:37] DEBUG ARM: makemkv.run <_io.TextIOWrapper name=9 encoding='UTF-8'>\n[08-03-2025 00:57:37] DEBUG ARM: makemkv.__init__ MakeMKV command: '/usr/local/bin/makemkvcon --robot --messages=-stdout info --cache=1 disc:9999'\n[08-03-2025 00:57:37] DEBUG ARM: makemkv.__init__ MakeMKV output: \n[08-03-2025 00:57:37] ERROR ARM: makemkv.__init__ Call to MakeMKV failed with code: 253\n```\n\nForum post:\n```\n[MakeMKV is free while in beta](https://forum.makemkv.com/forum/viewtopic.php?p=3548&sid=417bf48acf94b45f48ab4950fa20018a#p3548)\n\nPost by [mike admin](https://forum.makemkv.com/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&u=3&sid=417bf48acf94b45f48ab4950fa20018a) \u00bb Thu Mar 04, 2010 4:46 am\nAs stated on a main page all features of MakeMKV are free while program is in beta.\n\nThe current beta key is\n\nCode: [Select all](https://forum.makemkv.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=5&t=1053#)\n\nT-iyhMMBV8nWtNo3BgMdcvypH8UL01nYmww2zFzQDtiZsdJUOaAuCURsPRQ1Hj3i75RE\n\nand is valid until end of July 2025. Please check back for updated key on this page.\n```\n\nRunning `bash /opt/arm/scripts/update_key.sh` with my permanent key and commenting out `prep_mkv()` from `makemkv.py` was a successful workaround.\nWhere can I put the beta key? \nI don't have the update_key.sh.\n\nroot@ARM:/home/john# ls /opt/arm/scripts\nls: cannot access '/opt/arm/scripts': No such file or directory\nroot@ARM:/home/john#\n\n\nFound config file in .MakeMKV/settings.conf and put in key above. Still fails with same code.\n\nwill try restarting docker and see if that helps.\n\nStop and restart docker made no difference.\n\nBy the way, I don't see any mention of the key in the log. In the past, MakeMKV always said something about the key when it started up, I think. Don't have any old logs to look at but I seem to remember that.\n@Bigjohn4 This beta key will not work unless you set your system date back to July. It doesn't seem that a new beta key has been released. My workaround uses a purchased permanent key.\nI still suspect there's a bug in how ARM applies the registration key from the configuration that uses the beta key even when a permanent key is specified, but I haven't been able to spot it. \n> [@Bigjohn4](https://github.com/Bigjohn4) This beta key will not work unless you set your system date back to July. It doesn't seem that a new beta key has been released. My workaround uses a purchased permanent key.\n\nSeems like the timing is bad to get one of those, as the store link doesn't open for me to buy one \n\n<img width=\"1104\" height=\"347\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/abfebc33-ea89-4851-91d8-c5b3cc7f8a5d\" />\nAny updates on this issue. Seems like this is still broken when I try to Rip a DVD\n@showcasefloyd try @nickc01 's time travel workaround if you are using the beta key. That is not a problem with ARM. You'll just need to wait until the MakeMVK maintainer updates it.\n\nIf you have purchased a key, try the workaround I posted.\n@nickc01 after modifying the start_arm_container.sh, I am still getting the exact same error. Is there any way to check if ARM is pulling from the new image? I also saw that you can change the key manually by updating the config file in .MakeMKV/settings.conf, but I thought that there was an auto-updater for the beta key built into ARM. Either way, I guess I'm trying to figure out if my system is really using the correct key, and actually running the updated image.\n\n*I also tried changing the system time as suggested by @mantistobagganmd , but I get the following error:  \n\nERROR ARM: <urlopen error [SSL: CERTIFICATE_VERIFY_FAILED] certificate verify failed: certificate is not yet valid (_ssl.c:1007)>\n\nI'm thinking this may be from the OMDb server but that's really just a guess.\n\n***I must add that I am a complete noob in linux and docker, I have been learning as I go just to install ARM lol.\n> [@nickc01](https://github.com/nickc01) after modifying the start_arm_container.sh, I am still getting the exact same error. Is there any way to check if ARM is pulling from the new image? I also saw that you can change the key manually by updating the config file in .MakeMKV/settings.conf, but I thought that there was an auto-updater for the beta key built into ARM. Either way, I guess I'm trying to figure out if my system is really using the correct key, and actually running the updated image.\n> \n> *I also tried changing the system time as suggested by [@mantistobagganmd](https://github.com/mantistobagganmd) , but no dice\n> \n> ***I must add that I am a complete noob in linux and docker, I have been learning as I go just to install ARM lol.\n\nIf you are getting the same 253 error code, then ARM is probably still using the old image instead of the new one. You can run these commands to remove the container and rebuild it with the new image:\n\n```sh\ndocker stop arm-rippers\n\ndocker rm arm-rippers\n```\n\nThis assumes that in your start_arm_container.sh, the \"--name\" field is set to \"arm-rippers\". If it's something else, then use that name in the commands instead. You can then try ./start_arm_container.sh and see if anything changes.\nAh I see, cant believe I forgot about that smh. I rebuilt the container, and now I am getting:\n\nERROR ARM: Call to MakeMKV failed with code: 11\n\nIt seems that the rebuild probably fixed the key expiration, as I am getting error 11 instead of error 253.\n\n> Ah I see, cant believe I forgot about that smh. I rebuilt the container, and now I am getting:\n> \n> ERROR ARM: Call to MakeMKV failed with code: 11\n> \n> It seems that the rebuild probably fixed the key expiration, as I am getting error 11 instead of error 253.\n\nI'm somehow getting stuck at code 11 too. \n\nWhen I call makemkvcon directly on my system (using the libfaketime method), it's now complaining about RPC protection or Copy protection and reporting 0 titles, even though I just had makemkv working on my system yesterday. \n\n```\nmakemkvcon info disc:1\nMakeMKV v1.18.1 linux(x64-release) started\nUsing direct disc access mode\nDrive DVD+R-DL TSSTcorp CDDVDW SH-224DB SB00 R9636YAD401WYR has RPC protection that can not be bypassed. Change drive region or update drive firmware from http://tdb.rpc1.org. Errors likely to follow.\nCalculated BUP offset for VTS #0 does not match one in IFO header.\nCalculated BUP offset for VTS #1 does not match one in IFO header.\nIFO file for VTS #1 is corrupt, VOB file must be scanned. This may take very long time, please be patient.\nCalculated BUP offset for VTS #2 does not match one in IFO header.\nCalculated BUP offset for VTS #3 does not match one in IFO header.\nCalculated BUP offset for VTS #4 does not match one in IFO header.\nCalculated BUP offset for VTS #5 does not match one in IFO header.\nCalculated BUP offset for VTS #6 does not match one in IFO header.\nCalculated BUP offset for VTS #7 does not match one in IFO header.\nCalculated MVOB offset for VTS #0 does not match one in IFO header.\nFailed to open disc\nTotal 0 titles\n```\n\n\n```\n\u276f makemkvcon info disc:0\nMakeMKV v1.18.1 linux(x64-release) started\nUsing direct disc access mode\nEvaluation version, 29 day(s) out of 30 remaining\nLoaded content hash table, will verify integrity of M2TS files.\nThis disc uses newer version of AACS protection. Please let us know about it by visiting http://www.makemkv.com/a/?\nError 'Scsi error - ILLEGAL REQUEST:COPY PROTECTION KEY EXCHANGE FAILURE - AUTHENTICATION FAILURE' occurred while issuing SCSI command A30..0020074C100720..0CFAB42794F8F044B964411D9A894BE7826 to device 'SG:dev_21:4'\nError 'Scsi error - ILLEGAL REQUEST:COPY PROTECTION KEY EXCHANGE FAILURE - AUTHENTICATION FAILURE' occurred while issuing SCSI command A30..0020074C100720..099890C0AD9971D4901EDFFEC9581AB90DE to device 'SG:dev_21:4'\nError 'Scsi error - ILLEGAL REQUEST:COPY PROTECTION KEY EXCHANGE FAILURE - AUTHENTICATION FAILURE' occurred while issuing SCSI command A30..0020074C100720..06F08145728D476767DE88F67FB0D8AE4CE to device 'SG:dev_21:4'\nError 'Scsi error - ILLEGAL REQUEST:COPY PROTECTION KEY EXCHANGE FAILURE - AUTHENTICATION FAILURE' occurred while issuing SCSI command A30..0020074C100720..0C28BA4B7BEE77CDA747D35334D6C8E3105 to device 'SG:dev_21:4'\nError 'Scsi error - ILLEGAL REQUEST:COPY PROTECTION KEY EXCHANGE FAILURE - AUTHENTICATION FAILURE' occurred while issuing SCSI command A30..0020074C100720..0BC16A2A09826F4A7310A852D63B6D81481 to device 'SG:dev_21:4'\nError 'Scsi error - ILLEGAL REQUEST:COPY PROTECTION KEY EXCHANGE FAILURE - AUTHENTICATION FAILURE' occurred while issuing SCSI command A30..0020074C100720..01A49802A665C1A83FFD4C068C97F47CA0B to device 'SG:dev_21:4'\n```\n\nThat's very interesting. How would I call makemkvcon directly (specific commands) so that I can try to replicate what you have? Additionally, if you look at the ARM web interface when you insert your disc, does the title get recognized there? \n\nWhen I start a rip, ARM recognizes it immediately and starts reading the disc, but as soon as the actual rip starts, thats when I get the fatal error.\n\nI'm also wondering if this issue is related to the absence of system maintenance on the makemkv server, as I know mike (admin) has disappeared.\n> That's very interesting. How would I call makemkvcon directly (specific commands) so that I can try to replicate what you have? Additionally, if you look at the ARM web interface when you insert your disc, does the title get recognized there?\n> \n> When I start a rip, ARM recognizes it immediately and starts reading the disc, but as soon as the actual rip starts, thats when I get the fatal error.\n> \n> I'm also wondering if this issue is related to the absence of system maintenance on the makemkv server, as I know mike (admin) has disappeared.\n\nI was able to call it directly on my system by using this command:\n```sh\nenv FAKETIME=\"2025-07-27 03:01:29\" FAKETIME_DONT_FAKE_MONOTONIC=1 FAKETIME_NO_SIMULATE_SIGSEGV=1 LD_PRELOAD=/usr/lib64/libfaketime.so /usr/bin/makemkvcon\n```\n\nI made it easier for myself by creating a script called `/usr/bin/makemkvcon_fixed` so I can just use `makemkvcon_fixed` instead:\n```sh\n#!/bin/sh\n\nenv FAKETIME=\"2025-07-31 03:01:29\" FAKETIME_DONT_FAKE_MONOTONIC=1 FAKETIME_NO_SIMULATE_SIGSEGV=1 LD_PRELOAD=/usr/lib64/libfaketime.so /usr/bin/makemkvcon $@\n```\n\nIf you are planning on running this command on your system, the actual location of `libfaketime.so` and `makemkvcon` may vary. You can run `whereis libfaketime.so` and `whereis makemkvcon` to find out the exact locations, and modify the command with the correct locations.\n\nIf you want to run makemkvcon in the docker container, you can use this to enter into the container:\n```sh\ndocker exec -it arm-rippers bash\n```\n\nThen you can just run `makemkvcon` from there. My docker image patches makemkvcon with faketime, so you don't have to use the FAKETIME env variables or LD_PRELOAD when inside the docker container.\nI finally managed to get ARM (Automatic Ripping Machine) working again with MakeMKV, even after the betakey expired. Here\u2019s what I had to do:\n\n* Set the makemkv **perma key** (`MAKEMKV_PERMA_KEY`) to the current (dead) beta key, so ARM/MakeMKV will at least try to run.\n* Force the **Docker container time AND the host system time** to be exactly `\"2025-07-27 03:01:29\"` (any mismatch can break it).\n* **Bypass SSL certificate errors** inside ARM, because with a fake/old system time, HTTPS calls will fail otherwise.\n\n**AND IT NOW RIPS DVDs!**\n---\n\nHere is my `docker-compose.yaml`:\n```yaml\nversion: \"3.7\"\nservices:\n  arm-rippers:\n    image: nickc0101/arm_mkv_faketime:latest\n    container_name: arm-rippers\n    restart: always\n    privileged: true\n    command: >\n      bash -c \"sed -i '1iimport ssl' /opt/arm/arm/ui/metadata.py &&\n               sed -i '2issl._create_default_https_context = ssl._create_unverified_context' /opt/arm/arm/ui/metadata.py &&\n               date -s '2025-07-27 03:01:29' &&\n               /sbin/my_init\"\n    environment:\n      - ARM_UID=1001           # set your user ID\n      - ARM_GID=1002           # set your group ID\n      - TZ=Europe/Paris        # set your timezone\n    volumes:\n      - /home/arm:/home/arm\n      - /home/arm/music:/home/arm/music\n      - /home/arm/logs:/home/arm/logs\n      - /home/arm/media:/home/arm/media\n      - /home/arm/config:/etc/arm/config\n    devices:\n      - /dev/sr0:/dev/sr0\n      - /dev/sr1:/dev/sr1\n    ports:\n      - \"8080:8080\"\n    cpuset: \"0-24\"\n```\n\n---\nAnd if you need it, here\u2019s the **reset script** I use to ensure everything is clean and the date is always correct (run it via `cron` at 4am and/or at reboot):\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# reset_arm.sh\n\n# Set fake system date BEFORE restarting ARM\nFAKE_DATE=\"2025-07-27 03:01:29\"\ndate -s \"$FAKE_DATE\"\n\n# Delete ARM's DB to reset state (optional)\nrm -f /home/arm/db/arm.db\n\n# Restart the ARM Docker container\ndocker restart arm-rippers\n```\nThis combo finally got everything working again for me, even with expired keys.\n\n\n@ThePastPlayer This is very helpful, do you mind creating breaking your solution down into a walkthrough? I don't know a lot about how docker works and I'm struggling to get mine working. I'm sure this will be helpful to many others as it seems that this is the only way that most people will be able to use ARM unless makemkv is fixed or an update is pushed to ARM with these fixes. Thanks!\nI tried this again without doing all the change date stuff, and MakeMKV still failed with code 253.\nIs the MakeMKV team no longer working? \n\n[08-20-2025 15:10:23] INFO ARM: ************* Ripping disc with MakeMKV *************\n[08-20-2025 15:10:23] INFO ARM: Updating MakeMKV key...\n[08-20-2025 15:10:23] INFO ARM: Starting MakeMKV rip. Method is mkv\n[08-20-2025 15:10:24] ERROR ARM: Call to MakeMKV failed with code: 253\n[08-20-2025 15:10:24] INFO ARM: MakeMKV info exits.\n[08-20-2025 15:10:24] ERROR ARM: MakeMKV did not complete successfully.  Exiting ARM! Error: Call to MakeMKV failed with code: 253\nI still have no resolution. I have tried opening a case with MakeMKV forum, but no help from them either.\nHi BigJohn4. I can understand your frustration that you just expressed in #1501 in order to get attention. Your goal seems to just get ARM working and I am sorry that your are struggeling, so I will ignore the necroposting at this point.\n\nYour ticket was about the MakeMKV Error 253. I see in #1501 that you now managed to set your log output to debug. Congrats. This is crucial in order for us to determine what your problem actually is.\n\n> [08-03-2025 00:57:37] DEBUG ARM: makemkv.run MSG:5021,131332,1,\"This application version is too old.  Please download the latest version at http://www.makemkv.com/ or enter a registration key to continue using the current version.\",\"This application version is too old.  Please download the latest version at %1 or enter a registration key to continue using the current version.\",\"http://www.makemkv.com/\"\n\nAs of the Error in the Ticket, it was likely caused by either a wrong/expired beta key or a wrong perma key. So 3 possible problems could be the root cause.\n\n- Correct Perma Key, still getting the Error -> MakeMKV currently suggests to explicitly use the beta key and not the perma key in these occasions.\n- Previously working but now expired Beta Key and MakeMKV site is down or purchase for a perma key cannot be done --> you may go for the described time work-around or just wait until and watch the forum page until the new key gets released.\n- Invalid Key or Don't have a key at all: Delete the Key entry in the settings and re-run the script to fetch the beta key.\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/automatic-ripping-machine/automatic-ripping-machine/commit/d3eeacc866e7ec462eb2688e24da479a776a3f58", "https://github.com/automatic-ripping-machine/automatic-ripping-machine/commit/e3437ab4ace88b51f45306831667ac474ae11504", "https://github.com/automatic-ripping-machine/automatic-ripping-machine/commit/7b6816c9afd9b4392ae304b64ef7b99722075f26"], "created_at": "2025-08-07T17:23:38Z"}
{"repo": "automatic-ripping-machine/automatic-ripping-machine", "pull_number": 1507, "instance_id": "automatic-ripping-machine__automatic-ripping-machine-1507", "issue_numbers": [1506], "base_commit": "d842f9a46851198b61e9d59bfc5f7aaab3f73e0a", "patch": "diff --git a/VERSION b/VERSION\nindex 61dc3342f..26452813e 100755\n--- a/VERSION\n+++ b/VERSION\n@@ -1,1 +1,1 @@\n-2.18.2\n+2.18.3\ndiff --git a/arm/ui/json_api.py b/arm/ui/json_api.py\nindex 4dbb730e0..ac254d6ca 100755\n--- a/arm/ui/json_api.py\n+++ b/arm/ui/json_api.py\n@@ -415,41 +415,55 @@ def abandon_job(job_id):\n         db.session.commit()\n         return json_return\n \n+    # Kill the process id\n+    job = Job.query.get(int(job_id))\n+    job.status = JobState.FAILURE.value\n     try:\n-        # Get job id\n-        job = Job.query.get(int(job_id))\n-        # Stop job process id (pid)\n-        job.status = JobState.FAILURE.value\n-        job_process = psutil.Process(job.pid)\n-        job_process.terminate()  # or p.kill()\n-        # release job from drive\n-        job.drive.release_current_job()\n-        notification = Notifications(f\"Job: {job_id} was Abandoned!\",\n-                                     f'Job with id: {job_id} was successfully abandoned. No files were deleted!')\n-        db.session.add(notification)\n-        db.session.commit()\n-        json_return['success'] = True\n-        app.logger.debug(f\"Job {job_id} was abandoned successfully\")\n-        job.eject()\n-    except psutil.NoSuchProcess:\n-        db.session.rollback()\n-        json_return['Error'] = f\"Couldn't find job.pid - {job.pid}! Reverting db changes.\"\n-        app.logger.debug(f\"Couldn't find job.pid - {job.pid}! Reverting db changes.\")\n-    except psutil.AccessDenied:\n-        db.session.rollback()\n-        json_return['Error'] = f\"Access denied abandoning job: {job.pid}! Reverting db changes.\"\n-        app.logger.debug(f\"Access denied abandoning job: {job.pid}! Reverting db changes.\")\n-    except Exception as error:\n+        terminate_process(job.pid)\n+    except Exception as err:\n         db.session.rollback()\n-        app.logger.debug(f\"Job {job_id} couldn't be abandoned. - {error}\")\n-        json_return[\"Error\"] = str(error)\n-    if 'Error' in json_return:\n-        notification = Notifications(f\"Job ERROR: {job_id} couldn't be abandoned\", json_return[\"Error\"])\n-        db.session.add(notification)\n-        db.session.commit()\n+        json_return[\"Error\"] = str(err)\n+        json_return['success'] = False\n+        title = f\"Job ERROR: {job.pid} couldn't be abandoned.\"\n+        message = json_return['Error']\n+        app.logger.debug(f\"{title} - Reverting db changes - {message}\")\n+        notification = Notifications(title, message)\n+    else:\n+        job.eject()  # only release/eject the job if the process got killed.\n+        json_return['success'] = True\n+        title = f\"Job: {job.pid} was Abandoned!\"\n+        message = f'Job with id: {job.pid} was successfully abandoned. No files were deleted!'\n+        notification = Notifications(title, message)\n+    db.session.add(notification)\n+    db.session.commit()\n     return json_return\n \n \n+def terminate_process(pid):\n+    \"\"\"\n+    Terminates the process associated with a given pid.\n+    :param pid: Process ID (int)\n+    :raises: ValueError if access is denied\n+    \"\"\"\n+    if pid is None:\n+        message = \"PID not found for job.\"\n+        app.logger.warning(message)\n+        return\n+    try:\n+        job_process = psutil.Process(pid)\n+        job_process.terminate()  # or job_process.kill()\n+    except psutil.NoSuchProcess:\n+        message = f\"Process id {pid} was not found. Job has already been terminated.\"\n+        app.logger.warning(message)\n+        # No raise here. No process is a terminated process.\n+    except psutil.AccessDenied as err:\n+        message = f\"Access denied abandoning job: {pid}!\"\n+        app.logger.error(message)\n+        raise ValueError(message) from err\n+    else:\n+        app.logger.debug(f\"Job with PID {pid} was terminated.\")\n+\n+\n def change_job_params(config_id):\n     \"\"\"Update values for job\"\"\"\n     job = Job.query.get(config_id)\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "\ud83d\udc1b Cannot release Job after server restart\n### Is there an existing issue for this?\n\n- [x] I have searched the existing issues\n\n### I have checked the wiki\n\n- [x] I have searched the wiki for this problem\n\n### Does this issue exist in the latest version?\n\n- [x] I'm using the latest release\n\n### Describe the bug?\n\nAfter a server restart, unfinished ripping processes remain visible in the UI and cannot get abandoned. The only option is to delete the job from the database.\n\nThe root cause behind this is that the database still holds the old job id but since the server restartet, this process id is not valid anymore. Non existing Process ids can safely be assumed terminated:\n\nhttps://github.com/automatic-ripping-machine/automatic-ripping-machine/blob/f74d89af0371d9a8bfab81557184ecdc97e860f3/arm/ui/json_api.py#L434-L437\n\n### To Reproduce\n\nStart Job\nRestart Server\nPress Abandon in UI\n\n### What OS are you seeing the problem on?\n\nOther (please state in Anything else? section)\n\n### ARM Release Version or Git hash (You can find this in the arm settings page)\n\nUbuntu 22.04, f74d89af0371d9a8bfab81557184ecdc97e860f3 2.18.1\n\n### Expected behavior?\n\nAbandoning Jobs should work for otherwise terminated processes\n\n### Relevant log output\n\n```shell\n[2025-08-10 14:08:25,325] DEBUG ARM: json_api.abandon_job Couldn't find job.pid - 2121141! Reverting db changes.\n```\n\n### Anything else?\n\n_No response_\n\n### Code of Conduct\n\n- [x] I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/automatic-ripping-machine/automatic-ripping-machine/commit/6d2498da978aa43627244dfdb1d3c72c4c4c5249", "https://github.com/automatic-ripping-machine/automatic-ripping-machine/commit/567191860038ef358f1410414fe2f107bb8ebe99", "https://github.com/automatic-ripping-machine/automatic-ripping-machine/commit/5bd97df30def9e3766cc1b08b41e93f05519ca58"], "created_at": "2025-08-10T15:35:59Z"}
